<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-12-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-12-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="277" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d277">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 772.73/1:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                                </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-09">December
                                    9, 1918</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>4. For your information. Important. I have learned that on December 6th,
                            delegates from the Montenegrin Stuppina, 18 in number, left for Belgrade
                            to proclaim annexation to Serbia. It is confirmed by pro-Serbians that
                            Montenegro is discontented.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Nelson Page</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>